# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the code is
#   intended to run in multiple environments; otherwise, check them in:
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, if you're executing pipenv install --ignore-pipfile, you should ignore this file.
#   For details, see https://pipenv.pypa.io/en/latest/advanced/#pipfile-lock-security-considerations
#   Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Use poetry.lock instead of ignoring it
#   poetry.lock (highly recommended to check in poetry.lock)

